reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great battery life
reviews.reviewText: I was impressed with the battery life, it lasted all day at the State Fair, and on many other occasions. This was bought for use on a stroller, but I have also used it in the house when in the kitchen or at the computer desk. Nice strong fan, and the portable nature of it as well as the flexible legs makes it very handy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love this fan! One of the legs broke off but it still works well. Also fits in the diaper bag well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The item came exactly as shown. I like that it’s rechargeable, and the battery lasts long enough that it’s convenient to bring along. The legs are pliable enough that you can wrap them around the stroller handle. Overall worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this fan as a backup fan for my son’s stroller. Since the one he uses is really good, I started to use this one in the handle of the stroller in case I needed it in a hot day and it works good. The only thing is that I wish that the legs were better because I have to constantly adjust it in position. The battery life is great, never ran out of charge.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars We LOVE our fan!
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely LOVE this fan! I take my baby out in the stroller a lot so I needed a fan for the summer heat. I came across this one and we are obsessed. It lasts a long time on a single charge (long time=I haven’t charged it in a month). The fan actually blows cold air out, is quiet, and the rubber feature that attaches to the stroller works great! Comes with a usb charger and I usually will just charge it over night when needed. HIGHLY recommend if looking for a stroller fan this summer!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars NOT* Great for Peloton
reviews.reviewText: Update: stopped working completely and will not hold a charge or start trying to charge. We only used this for working out and it was plugged in to the peloton all the time. Annoying. Not repurchasing.I bought this to use on our Peloton and it works great! the battery life is amazing - I charge it once a week just because I HAVE to have a fan to work out, but I don't think I necessarily have to charge it that much? I use it daily for about an hour at a time. It has never died on me, which is amazing! My last fan I was using had to be charged every 2 uses or it would spontaneously go kaput. My husband left this one running overnight and I was able to still use it without a charge the next day! (We only use level 1 or 2 power though, for some reason I find with small fans that level 3 just kills the battery, but 1-2 are perfectly good and last forever.)Only minor issue is that it rattles - we thing the way it's set on the legs somehow or the clips on the side are the source of that noise. It's fine if you have headphones in or are working out and other noises going on, but my hubs has said when I'm working out with headphones, it bothers him if he's in the room. So, might be something to consider if you, like other reviewers, use it for a baby seat or something.
